Officials of three university workers' unions yesterday said they will continue with their strike until their demands are met.They said they would meet everyday at Egerton University's Njoro campus to discuss the way forward and ensure employees do not turn up for work.The Kenya Union of Domestic, Hotels, Educational Institutions, Hospitals and Allied Workers, the University Academic Staff Union and the Kenya University Staff Union said the government should intervene to end the strike. The unions have more than 3,000 members from Egerton university.